name: Appetite Classic

reviews.review_text:
Enjoy a breezy afternoon sipping on some beers or cocktails and Goan food on the first floor of this restaurant.

With the beautiful view of the town below, this probably is the selling point of this restaurant.

The food is good but the view is better.
Just spend a lazy afternoon here and enjoy your food.

We wanted to go for a rainy Sunday afternoon thali and had heard good things about this place. Unfortunately they don’t serve their thalis on Sunday.
We stayed for lunch anyway.

The service was quite relaxed in the typical Goan style, but it was worth the wait with the amazing prawn curry and prawn rava fry which were just outstanding and our favourites!

We also had silver fish fry, chinak fry -‘d surmai fry, along with some fish caldin.
These were all good, but not the best we’ve ever eaten.

What makes this place worth it is the prawn curry of course, but also the stunning views! It is in a gorgeous green location overlooking trees and was absolutely perfect in the monsoon!

They also have an AC section which would be great during the summers, but then you lose the views.

It’s a good option if you’re in mapusa and want a nice open space instead of being in a cramped restaurant.

The food was decent but the service was very slow . The waiter didn't even clear our plate once done with starters. We came through swiggy dine out and it was mentioned with free drink but the restaurant disagreed and caused a problem. The worst part was the serradura desert i had. It was just full of cream and only pinch of biscuit powder. It was very upsetting. Please improve on these points. Would love to change my reviews about it in the near future. Thank you.

description:
**Restaurant Review: Appetite Classic**

Nestled in the charming town of Mapusa, Appetite Classic stands out with an overall rating of 3.8 based on a compelling 1,200 reviews. This establishment has garnered attention for its delightful offerings, particularly seafood, with customers frequently highlighting dishes such as prawn curry and fish preparations. Featured tags such as "fish" (21 mentions), "dinner" (18 mentions), and "quantity" (15 mentions) illustrate the restaurant's strengths and specialties, hinting at a diverse menu that appeals to lovers of Goan cuisine.

**Ambiance & Design**

Walking into Appetite Classic, guests are greeted with breezy, open-air seating that enhances the dining experience. The first-floor location offers stunning views of the town, making for an ideal setting to sip on refreshing beers or cocktails while savoring Goan delicacies. Lush green surroundings create a tranquil atmosphere, particularly enchanting during monsoons when patrons can enjoy the scenic beauty from within. Photos reveal an inviting space adorned with a vibrant palette and cozy yet spacious layout, perfect for leisurely afternoons filled with great food and conversation. The ambiance strikes a balance between casual comfort and scenic elegance.

**Menu & Culinary Experience**

Appetite Classic prides itself on a menu that features a variety of seafood dishes, with many recommending the prawn curry and prawn rava fry as must-tries. The culinary offerings are beautifully plated, showcasing the freshness of local ingredients that define Goan cuisine. Customers have raved about other highlights such as silver fish fry and chinak fry - ‘d surmai, but some have expressed that while the food is decent, it may not always reach the heights of culinary excellence they’ve experienced elsewhere. A notable mention is the restaurant's fish thali, though it is worth noting that it isn't available on Sundays, leaving some visitors disappointed yet willing to return. Furthermore, an air-conditioned section ensures comfort during the hotter months, although it sadly sacrifices the breathtaking views that the outdoor seating offers.

**Customer Experience & Service**

While many guests appreciate the relaxed, Goan-style service, others have noted instances of slowness, particularly with the clearing of plates. Experiences seem to vary, with some diners praising the friendly atmosphere while others encountered challenges, such as discrepancies with promotional offers and dissatisfaction with certain dessert preparations—specifically the serradura, which received criticism for lacking a balanced taste. The overall sentiment suggests that improved service efficiency could elevate the dining experience significantly, but the laid-back charm of Appetite Classic remains a draw for those looking to unwind.

**Popularity & Reviews**

Customer sentiment around Appetite Classic is mixed but generally leans towards positivity, with many tipping their hats to its scenic views and carefully curated seafood menu. The blend of outdoor charm and hearty meals has lent the restaurant a favorable presence on social media, highlighted by the beautiful images that capture moments spent enjoying delectable food amidst picturesque backdrops. While the restaurant hasn't yet garnered any notable awards or critic ratings, its reputation continues to grow within the local dining scene.

**Utilizing Visual Content**

The visual evidence supports the overall positive narrative surrounding Appetite Classic. Photos featuring vibrant food presentations, like the tantalizing prawn curry and golden-fried fish, reflect the culinary artistry that the kitchen offers. The images also capture the inviting space and delightful views that set the mood, showcasing why many patrons choose to spend lazy afternoons at this beloved establishment in Mapusa.

In conclusion, Appetite Classic is a restaurant that embodies the spirit of Goan dining, complete with scenic views and a menu that tempts food lovers, particularly those with a penchant for seafood. While service could stand to be more responsive, the overall experience remains enjoyable, making it a noteworthy stop for anyone in the area.
